The Managing Director of FAAN, Captain Rabiu Hamisu Yadudu, today, May 31, 2022 hosted the daily editors of the print and electronic media to a breakfast meeting to discuss areas of collaboration towards improving the nation’s aviation industry. In his opening remarks, Captain Yadudu noted that the meeting is aimed at consolidating on the robust relationship between FAAN and the media.He added that the Authority shall continue to hold these kind of meetings on a regular basis going forward. http://www.faan.gov.ng The MD stated that the meeting is an interactive one and that participants should feel free to ask him questions in any area of airport operations. There were questions on concessioning, privatisation, facilities and infrastructure. All the questions were satisfactorily answered. READ ALSO THIS: SAHCO acquires more electric ground support equipment Captain Yadudu also used the opportunity to invite the media community to the FAAN National Aviation Conference (FNAC) holding from the 14th to 17th June, 2022 at the International Conference Centre, Abuja. The Conference will focus on sharing ideas and information, as well as apprising potential investors with opportunities available in the Nigerian aviation industry. FAAN…… Committed to our core values of Safety, Security and Comfort.